metadata.name: Guiding Light / Lost in Stillness #34
metadata.description:
Sometimes one can be lost. Not knowing where to go, frozen to action, as if any movement could be fatal against the unknown.

Then it all clicks. It may be due to a new tought, or due to the words of a loved one, it may even click thanks to the beauty of a flock of birds flying against the sky.
With a clear destination and renewed courage, the once lost can now resume their journey.


---

Made in Cables.gl


Press "P" to save a 15 second .webm video

Process can be a little wonky, and unfortunately only webm support

metadata.name: Fictional Cityscapes #100
metadata.description:
Some of the most stunning, and beloved, images are large cities, viewed from afar at the right angle, and preferably with some water in front. 

This project comes from my experiments with line art, and is slightly inspired by Hevey's amazing Dencity drop, which is on a different level to most generative art. 

The cities here are based on some fictional tower architecture and some unusual skies.

metadata.name: Annihilate This Week #80
metadata.description:
This is a companion piece to "Saturday Night's Alright (For Fighting)" (project #14045). Same algorithm of the previous one, only slightly modified, the main difference is that here the daily variations are all mixed up together and the output doesn't change based on the current day.

This is intended to be a gift for all collectors and the community of fx(hash) that showed so much support for the "Saturday" project, really beyond my expectations.

50% of the royalties goes to the minter, do with the piece whatever you'd like, hold it, sell or trade it, or even burn it if you really don't like it :)

Thank you!

----

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Oddball #27
metadata.description:
Oddball is an expansion of the piece I created for day 7 of Genuary 2023. The prompt: Sample a color palette from your favorite movie/album cover. All seven palettes in this project were sampled from the album cover for Insolito by Tipper (https://tipper.bandcamp.com/album/insolito). 

The project title is a play on insolito meaning "unusual" and the featured bubble-like cellular noise. These bubbles are used to warp low-frequency simplex noise. When combined with the vibrant palettes, striking psychedelic patterns appear.

Controls:

[space] or click to toggle animation
[r] to reset animation to static view
[s] to save as 4000x4000 PNG
[t] to toggle paper texture

metadata.name: Bricks & Books #46
metadata.description:
Civil engineering and reading, two passions, two disciplines, numbers and letters. Construction and literature, two vocations so different and yet with such close souls.
They are both represented here by Bricks and Books paying a symbolic tribute to construction and literature in one collection.
The challenge was keeping them together in the same piece of code to be able to maintain the strength of the message and the aesthetic of the creation.

metadata.name: Lands #69
metadata.description:
Lands are a group of artworks creating a minimalist and abstract satellite view. The earth is changing, more and more, day after day, the satellite views are a great proof of that. Stay aware and be careful is important.

I wanted to representing something real, linked with my values, and keep a beautiful composition and colors harmony.‚Ä® I worked with a new fresh touch for the colors management.

The size, position and frequency of the pieces are generated for each token, along with the color theme. 

Features : 
- piecesCount : the number of circles and rectangles.
- glitchLinesCount :  the number of lines behind the shapes.
- MultipleGlitchDirections : if the directions of the lines behind are just horizontal or vertical, or both (10% of chance to have only one direction)‚Ä®.

‚Ä®Handmade by code with Javascript, made with fragment.tools
‚Ä®Quentin Hocd√©, Brussels (Belgium), 2023.
